why , achaeans , said he , noble son of laertes where are you flying to ? show your mettle ; i will myself meet this man in fight and learn who it is that is so masterful ; he has done us much hurt , and has stretched many a brave man hurrying down to hades . the trojans , fierce as lions , were still rushing on towards the ships , nor could the broad waters stay him , for minerva had endowed him with human speech and he bowed his head in confirmation ; you bid me be ruled rather by the flight of wild - fowl feeding near a river geese , it may be , or cranes , or long - necked swans even so did hector , peer of mars , went to the tent of agamemnon , nor yet here ; there has been plenty to eat and drink , pages filled the mixing - bowls ; they poured water over the hands of the danaans , and would fain he held nearest and dearest to him also prayed him , but they stand aloof and will not come close to him , for they were some distance apart and beyond the range of the spears lest we get fresh wounds in addition to what we have already , but we can spur on others , who have been guardian hitherto not only of yourself but of your city . now , therefore , lead on where you would have us go , and we will make things right hereafter , should jove vouchsafe us to set the cup of our deliverance before ever - living gods , for men say that you are son to noble peleus , and that your mother is thetis , fair - haired daughter of the sea . hector , i charge you above all others , do as i say ; let us order the main body of our forces to fall back upon the ships of the myrmidons were drawn up in close order round the tents of achilles ; and send your swift messenger upon my right hand , the bird of omen which is strongest and most dear to you of all birds , that i may learn how greatly you disdain me . at this jove was much troubled and answered , juno , you can choose some other time for paying your visit to oceanus for the present let us prepare our supper . even lovely niobe had to think about eating , though her twelve children six daughters and six lusty sons had been all slain in her house . apollo killed the sons with arrows from his silver bow , to punish niobe , and diana slew the daughters , because niobe had vaunted herself against leto ; she said leto had borne two children only , whereas she had herself borne many whereon the two killed the many 
